Greetings from level 60,<br>
<br>
I just got flagged last week and still haven't zoned in to PoV or PoS. I've been thinking about trying to single kite frogs in PoS. I have about 3800 unbuffed mana ft4 scm1 and ID3 and always use mage earing and KEI.<br>
<br>
First.....do I have the firepower using ISoS and draught of fire to do this?<br>
<br>
Next.....do you think the xp would be worth it? I currently quad geonids in WL and make a lot of cash (engraved royal velium armor) and toilers<br>
<br>
If you answered yes to questions 1 and 2......do you have any advice? I'm told they are near the zone in. Are there adds or any good places to bring them etc. etc. what are the basics of this camp? <br>
<br>
Thanks so much! <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=543402</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merdin>Merdin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/15/03 2:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> untill you have SCM 2 ide suggest you dont use any draughts, just ISoS, i have about 3550 mana SCM2 and FT2 and it takes me 80%ish useing just ISoS, draughts just arent good enough untill you have the PoP ones, and yes its worth it, about 4 mins per kill and 10% AA or 5% lvl each (about)<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;edit&gt;&gt;<br>
Forgot to mention, i have mana preservation 3 as well, you may have to med kite the last nuke or 2 if ya dont, before i had SCM2 i had to med kite the last nuke too. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merdin>Merdin</A> at: 5/15/03 2:18:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuratuli>Zuratuli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> Yeah it won't be a fly in the park... Get focus items before ya do it. I'd suggest a using mostly icespear for efficientcy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 10:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> This might have an obvious answer but I'll ask anyhow.<br>
<br>
I was grouping on them, and not actually pulling in PoV on frogs.  Half of them were immune to changes in run speed...<br>
<br>
I was planning on rooting/nuking etc. to burn down the frog.<br>
<br>
How do you know what frogs to pull?  <br>
<br>
How many hitpoints do they have exactly?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quikpick>Quikpick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 647<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 1:27 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> Delfontes, there are two different types of frogs. The ones in PoV can be rarely snared, the ones in PoS are good soloing mobs. <p><p><P><p align="center"><strong><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55973"><font color="#00CC00">Sage Quikpick Emberlore</a></font><BR><font color="#999999">Sorceress of Chronology</font></strong><BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=delfontes>Delfontes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 3:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> You know, that explains a lot.  I thought I had heard about frogs in PoS, but I haven't ever seen them there.  Killed a lot of Daiku, and giants, but never explored, always with a raid type force to try for BoT/Tactics key pieces. <br>
<br>
/apo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merdin>Merdin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 7:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> you can kill the ZI ones, if ya pull at the right angle u can get a few without adds, but the generaly killed ones are the forest frogs around where the forest giants and bee trees are, just dont aggro any bees or giants, pull strategy? just snare it and if its resisted run really really far then resnare or root and snare. <p>Baron Merdin Knighteye<br>
60th Sorcerer<br>
My stuff at:<br>
<br>
http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=495173<br>
<br>
Borras Dmunk<br>
48 monk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caldaer>Caldaer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 8:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> If you get adds.. just root them and keep running. They will forget you pretty easy. Just run your frog away from them and all is good. Abscond after solo'ing to clear agro.<br>
<br>
-Caldaer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 9:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pfffttt</span><hr size=1> Entrance frogs are already camped enough by rangers, druids, and bards, don't give away all the secrets.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merdin>Merdin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 8:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice on Single kiting Frogs</span><hr size=1> cant forget necros taelen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Baron Merdin Knighteye<br>
