<br>
Borras Dmunk<br>
48 monk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mtw333>mtw333</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 11:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Druids and Necros know about the ones in the back, at least on Tunare =\<br>
<br>
As far as original poster goes, it can be done with ISoS which uses less mana but also less damage, which equals more time, at least one more snare, etc etc. You will more than likely spend plenty of medding time during the fight as well. I know my tank of mana is at least 4500-4800 @ 61 and I usually have to root/med for one more Sunstrike (I have no AAs yet that effect damage or mana conservation). A good way to determine how you are doing is to compare your mana bar to the frog's hps @ 75%, 50% &amp; 25% left, of your mana. If the frog's hps bar is about the same, you will do pretty well with a full tank. The bigger the difference between your mana and his hps, the more you are going to be root/medding etc etc.<br>
<br>
***Side note, DO NOT GET HIT by them if you can avoid it at all. They drop manaskin in one round in addition to actually doing some damage on you and there is a possiblity when they do hit you that a nasty dot will land. One possibility is to leave a slot open and cancel magic on yourself, I guess, but that dot left me with 1.5 bubbles of health left compared to full hps when it landed &lt;he only hit me for an additional 7 damage after manaskin dropped. My friend said the hits are 400-600 (?) and it backstabs as well. The attack is somewhere between a double to quad, not sure as it only had to nail me once with that dot for me to avoid getting tagged again, LoL. Since I had used all my mana in addition to root/medding, I didn't have the mana to try and dispell the dot... DO NOT GET HIT and you can avoid all that. <br>
Also, try to kite them as close to the zone wall as possible to avoid adding more frogs... They spawn any where from close to the giant fortress to the trees back near the named mob in the corner... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 12:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> to the original question....</span><hr size=1> With what you have described you should be able to solo the loroks further in or the nopthans at the entrance, but like one posted said do not get hit.  Keep up manaskin or epic.  The big and small frogs have pretty much exactly the same hp's, the only real difference is the big ones will go into flee mode when low on health which can suck if you get too much distance because they will regen FAST.  The small frogs will not run and you can be further away from them without them going into regen mode.<br>
<br>
I suspect you will have to med kite some.  I am level 65 with below average gear and MP3, SCF3, SCM1, FT3, and I always have KEI.  I don't have ID3 nor do I use a mage bracer.  I solo with ISoS which is focused with Iceflame and PoP draughts unfocused.  I cast one ISoS for every 2 pop draughts.  PoP draughts NEVER get resisted and ISoS does get resisted marginally frequently.  I always use harvest of druzzil and am usually near oom or have to med kite a little bit.  Before the horse nerf I never had to med kite...  but now I don't kite using my horse because I only have the 10k model.  Being mounted when casting during a kite makes a big difference...  so get a 50k+ horse if you can afford it...  that is what I am saving for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=901.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=901.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=901.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  